<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Bogan Elementary School News</title><link>https://www.talawanda.org/</link><description>News and announcements from Bogan Elementary School, including events, activities, and important dates.</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>Talawanda Enews RSS Converter</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 14 Nov 2025 03:35:35 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Food Resources Available for Families</title><link>https://app.smore.com/n/59vme-bogan-weekly-news#bh1mh3rers</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Due to uncertainty about SNAP benefits in November, Talawanda is sharing food resource options:
- &lt;strong&gt;Little Free Pantry&lt;/strong&gt; - Located outside main entrance at Bogan, restocked daily
- &lt;strong&gt;Backpack Program&lt;/strong&gt; - Small bag of food for students every Thursday
- &lt;strong&gt;Family Food Boxes&lt;/strong&gt; - Can be picked up or delivered within 24 hours
- &lt;strong&gt;Community Pantries&lt;/strong&gt; - Additional resources linked in the flyer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For help accessing these resources, contact Emily White, Bogan Social Worker at 513-273-3403 or whitee@talawanda.org&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://app.smore.com/n/59vme-bogan-weekly-news#bh1mh3rers"&gt;View original newsletter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">bh1mh3rers-bs71fyqtkv-by1drppofy</guid><pubDate>Fri, 07 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Lost and Found Reminder Before Winter Break</title><link>https://app.smore.com/n/59vme-bogan-weekly-news#bjqvo7kz71</link><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;lost and found is filling up&lt;/strong&gt; with lunchboxes and clothing items. Students who have misplaced items should check the lost and found soon. &lt;strong&gt;Any unclaimed items will be donated after winter break.&lt;/strong&gt; Parents are reminded to &lt;strong&gt;label their child's belongings with their name&lt;/strong&gt; to help return lost items.&lt;/p&gt;
