&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;November menus are now available&lt;/strong&gt; for breakfast and lunch. The breakfast menu includes items like Mini Chocolate Chip French Toast, Breakfast Bowls, Chocolate Donut Holes, Sausage &amp;amp; Cheese Biscuit Sandwiches, and more throughout the month. 100% fruit juice, assorted fruit selection, and milk are included with every breakfast. The cafeteria is closed November 24-25 and 27-28 for Thanksgiving break.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://app.smore.com/n/zqt8c-bogan-weekly-news#b0srpil80f"&gt;View original newsletter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">b0srpil80f-b570fb3xuh-bfr77vevhd-bkdkrlbhb6</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>When to Stay Home from School</title><link>https://app.smore.com/n/bhjc1-bogan-weekly-news#bfk3x3z2v4</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Cold and flu season guidelines for keeping sick children home have been updated. &lt;strong&gt;Stay home if your child has:&lt;/strong&gt; a fever of 100Â°F or higher, frequent/continual coughing or difficulty breathing, diarrhea or vomiting, body rash with fever, active head lice, eye infection with discharge, or sore throat with congestion. &lt;strong&gt;Return to school when:&lt;/strong&gt; fever-free for 24 hours without medication, symptoms are improving, and specific condition requirements are met (e.g., 24 hours after starting antibiotic eye drops, tolerating food for 12 hours after vomiting). If your child is absent, call the attendance line and submit any doctor's notes to the front office. For COVID-19, students can return when fever-free for 24 hours without medication and symptoms are minimal and improving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://app.smore.com/n/bhjc1-bogan-weekly-news#bfk3x3z2v4"&gt;View original newsletter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">bfk3x3z2v4-bh5d58n7on-bpa863204d</guid><pubDate>Fri, 24 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>2025-2026 Yearbook Sales Now Open</title><link>https://app.smore.com/n/bhjc1-bogan-weekly-news#b2pmshiux7</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Yearbook sales for the &lt;strong&gt;2025-2026 school year&lt;/strong&gt; have started early! &lt;/p&gt;
